02/05/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- International observers from the OSCE and the European Parliament will be monitoring the May 8th local elections.
The Central Election Commission (CEC) has officially approved the OSCE's request for 249 short-term observers who will join seven long-term observers.
The CEC also decided on Sunday (May 1st) that the European Parliament will contribute 11 observers on the day of the vote.
Foreign embassies will provide additional international monitoring:
The Netherlands has applied for 11 monitors while the US Embassy seeks 62 observers.
(Lajmifundit, Top News, Ora News - 01/05/11)
